node.text:
We’re celebrating #WorldCocktailDay with a MIN8® by @sonjijam of Palermo’s @13_bootleg. Featured in @50bestbars #PassTheShaker series, this highball twist provides the perfect refreshment for a spring evening.

MIN8®
50 ml Michter's US*1 Bourbon
15 ml Mancino Red Vermouth
1 dash bitters
Chinotto
Build in the glass (highball). Fill with chinotto. Stir. Garnish with orange zest.

#WorldCocktailDay #PassTheShaker #Worlds50BestBars #50BestBars #MakeItMichters #Michters #MichtersWhiskey

node.text:
Congratulations to Sydney, Australia’s own @maybe_sammy_sydney on winning the Michter’s Art of Hospitality Award 2020 at the @50bestbars.

Well done to @cato17, @martin_hudak , @andreagua, @sarah_proietti_ & @paolo_maffietti on earning this extremely well-deserved recognition!

#worlds50best #50bestbars #michters #michterswhiskey

node.title: Maybe Sammy wins Michter’s Art of Hospitality Award 2020

node.text:
Bar Manager @benjicavagna presents a Spano Butter cocktail for @50bestbars’ #passtheshaker series. At the height of the COVID-19 pandemic, the @1930cocktailbar team led a fundraising drive for the Bergamo healthcare system. Salute!

Recipe:
4 dashes of Homemade Old Fashioned Bitters
7.5ml Butter & Sarawak Pepper Syrup
45ml Michter’s US*1 Rye
30ml @ronmatusalem Insólito

node.text:
The Ontario oasis of hospitality where owner @tendingkennedy stirred up a Toronto (what else?) with Michter’s Rye for @50bestbars’ #passtheshaker series.

Recipe:
60ml Michter’s US*1 Rye
7.5ml Fernet
5ml Creme de Banane
3 dashes of Grapeseed Tincture

Stir over ice. Strain and finish with lemon zest.

node.text:
Summer's new drink: "Good Rye Morning" by @picturesandcocktails_ 

Good Rye Morning
2oz Michter’s US*1 Rye
2.5oz cold brew
.75oz chai syrup
2 drops of 18.21 Prohibition Aromatic Bitters

Fill Collins glass with ice, top ice with the bitters, chai syrup, then the Michter's US*1 Rye. Stir what's in the glass with a metal straw to incorporate. Finally, shake the cold brew to get some foam and top the cocktail with it. Garnish with a sprinkle of the chai spice blend on the foam.

node.text:
We're excited to announce that we will begin shipping our 2021 bottling of Toasted Barrel Finish Bourbon in September. This will mark the first release of the whiskey since August 2018.

“At Michter’s we do a lot of experimentation as we pursue our goal of making the greatest American whiskey. The innovative work that our production team is undertaking on toasted barrel finishing is delivering remarkable results,” commented Dan McKee, @michtersmasterdistiller. To make this special Toasted release, Michter’s starts with fully matured barrels of its US*1 Small Batch Kentucky Straight Bourbon and transfers the whiskey into a second barrel made of 18-month air dried wood for additional aging. The second barrel has been toasted to precise specifications, but not charred.

node.text:
Name a better duo. We'll wait.

Michter's Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies with US*1 Kentucky Straight Rye 
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies 

2 sticks unsalted butter, melted and cooled 
1/2 cup sugar 
1 cup light brown sugar
2 large eggs, room temperature 
1 tsp vanilla extract
3 tbsp Michter's US*1 Kentucky Straight Rye 
2 1/4 cups all purpose flour 
1 tsp coarse salt 
3/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda 
2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips 

Preheat oven to 350 degrees with racks in the upper and lower thirds. 

In a large bowl, whisk together butter and both sugars. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Whisk in vanilla and Michter's US*1 Kentucky Straight Rye. Stir in flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; mix until barely combined. Add chocolate chips and stir until evenly distributed. 

Scoop out 1/4 cup portions onto parchment-lined baking sheets, spacing about 3 inches apart. 

Bake, rotating pans halfway through, until cookies are golden around the edges, about 15 minutes.

It's cocktail time. 🍉🥃

I Carried A Watermelon
1.5 oz Michter’s US*1 American Whiskey
4 oz lemonade
1 oz of watermelon juice
 
Lightly shake all ingredients together and pour into a Pint or Collins glass with fresh ice. Garnish with a Watermelon wedge.
